283
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:08,740
Do you?

284
00:21:08,740 --> 00:21:10,360
Punch.

285
00:21:10,360 --> 00:21:12,100
Be brave!

286
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:14,260
I will go easy on you.

287
00:21:14,260 --> 00:21:19,580
If your hand touches anywhere on my face,

288
00:21:19,580 --> 00:21:22,060
then you're a winner.

289
00:21:22,060 --> 00:21:23,860
Do you have the guts?

290
00:21:23,860 --> 00:21:26,380
Punch.

291
00:21:26,380 --> 00:21:32,760
Go! Just Go!

292
00:21:55,760 --> 00:21:57,600
Jesus Christ!

293
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:01,460
Woah!

294
00:22:01,460 --> 00:22:02,780
I am sorry.

295
00:22:02,780 --> 00:22:05,040
It wasn't intentional.

296
00:22:15,060 --> 00:22:17,940
I forget my bag.

297
00:22:20,040 --> 00:22:22,920
I am going now. Goodbye, everyone.

298
00:22:23,800 --> 00:22:26,401
Hey! That was very insulting.

299
00:22:26,401 --> 00:22:28,800
Yeah! Let's go beat him up.

300
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,600
Let's go.

301
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:32,420
Stop!

302
00:22:33,540 --> 00:22:35,280
Just let him go.

303
00:22:41,020 --> 00:22:44,120
You became more determined, Thi.

304
00:22:44,120 --> 00:22:46,420
But next time, I won't go easy on you.

305
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:07,940
It doesn't hurt that much.

306
00:23:07,940 --> 00:23:11,900
Just a weak punch. I don't think he will be angry.

307
00:23:11,900 --> 00:23:14,040
I guess.

308
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:16,820
What if he's angry?

309
00:23:16,820 --> 00:23:21,860
The Watphlu Gang will…

310
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:25,960
Damn it! Why do I have to do this?

311
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:29,460
I can't do this anymore.

312
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:35,860
No! No!

313
00:23:35,860 --> 00:23:38,600
The hole is still shallow!

314
00:23:53,500 --> 00:23:57,200
I hope it won't be that bad.

315
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:09,100
- What should we have for the dinner?
- Anything.

316
00:24:09,100 --> 00:24:10,720
- What about Papaya Salad?
- Sure.

317
00:24:10,720 --> 00:24:12,700
Hey, Thi, do you want to join us?

318
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:14,700
Thi!

319
00:24:14,700 --> 00:24:16,420
Hey!

320
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:19,540
What's going on?

321
00:24:19,540 --> 00:24:23,200
I just ask if you want to have dinner with us.

322
00:24:24,050 --> 00:24:27,520
No, I have my tutoring class today.

323
00:24:27,520 --> 00:24:30,200
You guys can go ahead.

324
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:32,800
Oh, well. Okay.

325
00:24:33,580 --> 00:24:37,340
- What's going on with him?
- I don't know either.

326
00:24:37,340 --> 00:24:39,080
Let's go.

327
00:24:45,320 --> 00:24:46,740
Thi,

328
00:24:46,740 --> 00:24:51,160
can we go get our snacks?

329
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:53,860
Okay.

330
00:24:53,860 --> 00:24:57,100
Let's have a 15-minute break.

331
00:24:57,100 --> 00:24:58,520
Thank you.

332
00:24:58,520 --> 00:25:00,220
Let's go.

333
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:04,180
Hurry up.

334
00:25:19,540 --> 00:25:20,960
Hey, check this out.

335
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:22,540
What?

336
00:25:22,540 --> 00:25:25,041
Hey! Again?

337
00:25:25,041 --> 00:25:27,980
- The other one was seriously injured.
- I feel bad for him.

338
00:25:27,980 --> 00:25:30,060
That's scary.

339
00:25:30,060 --> 00:25:32,080
It's just nearby our school. Right?

340
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:34,641
- What happened?
- There is a big fight near our school.

341
00:25:34,641 --> 00:25:37,260
I see.

342
00:25:37,260 --> 00:25:41,560
- Right. Do you know Noey Watphlu?
- What?

343
00:25:41,560 --> 00:25:44,120
Don't tell me…

344
00:25:44,120 --> 00:25:46,500
the Watphlu Gang?

345
00:25:46,500 --> 00:25:48,460
Yes.

346
00:25:52,700 --> 00:25:56,700
Oh, it seems like you know them.

347
00:25:56,700 --> 00:25:58,460
I will tell you something.

348
00:25:58,460 --> 00:26:02,360
This gang walks past our school a lot.

349
00:26:02,360 --> 00:26:04,000
So scary!

350
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:09,520
But I think Noey Watphlu looks very cool though.

351
00:26:09,520 --> 00:26:13,320
That's right. But still scary anyway.

352
00:26:13,320 --> 00:26:15,660
Who would want to be around him?

353
00:26:15,660 --> 00:26:19,000
He's only a sophomore. Right?

354
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:21,100
Yeah, he is a sophomore.

355
00:26:21,100 --> 00:26:23,520
But I am not sure about other gang members,

356
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:26,040
Whether they are still in school or not.

357
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:28,820
No need to study. Being a gangster is way better.

358
00:26:28,820 --> 00:26:30,900
Yeah, that's right.

359
00:26:30,900 --> 00:26:33,200
You always said that.

360
00:26:34,740 --> 00:26:36,340
Well… but…

361
00:26:36,340 --> 00:26:39,300
How do you know that Noey and his gang?

362
00:26:39,300 --> 00:26:43,100
Nonsense! I don' t know him at all.

363
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:47,580
Are you ready to continue the lesson?

364
00:26:47,580 --> 00:26:49,640
Everyone is here now?

365
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:57,820
Ready.

366
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:12,020
Noey.

367
00:27:14,380 --> 00:27:16,510
Thi, I have to leave early today.

368
00:27:16,510 --> 00:27:18,680
My mom is calling me.

369
00:27:18,680 --> 00:27:20,740
You are leaving already?

370
00:27:25,040 --> 00:27:27,440
Three students left.

371
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:29,660
Four, including me.

372
00:27:30,540 --> 00:27:33,460
Thi, then I'd like to leave too.

373
00:27:33,460 --> 00:27:36,580
My dad doesn't want me to get home late today.

374
00:27:36,580 --> 00:27:39,220
Well, then, I'm leaving now.

375
00:27:39,220 --> 00:27:41,460
What a small world!

376
00:27:41,460 --> 00:27:43,780
Speaking of the devil.

377
00:27:43,780 --> 00:27:47,060
Can I take a photo with you, Noey? Just one photo.

378
00:27:47,060 --> 00:27:50,390
Let's go. What are you talking about?

379
00:27:50,390 --> 00:27:53,960
Can I take a photo, please?

380
00:27:53,960 --> 00:27:55,880
No, let's go.

381
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:57,120
Get the phone.

382
00:27:57,120 --> 00:27:59,920
See you again, Noey.

383
00:28:01,860 --> 00:28:04,640
Don't go…

384
00:28:15,740 --> 00:28:20,640
Well… I have to go now.

385
00:28:20,700 --> 00:28:24,780
My clothes are in a washing machine. I need to hang them up.

386
00:28:24,780 --> 00:28:27,420
Otherwise, they won't dry.

387
00:28:29,660 --> 00:28:31,960
Aren't you going to hang your clothes?

388
00:28:32,760 --> 00:28:34,900
I am leaving now.

389
00:28:35,900 --> 00:28:37,800
What?

390
00:28:37,800 --> 00:28:40,040
Why are you still here?

391
00:28:40,040 --> 00:28:41,940
I want to, but…

392
00:28:41,940 --> 00:28:44,020
But what?

393
00:28:44,020 --> 00:28:45,540
Huh?

394
00:28:47,640 --> 00:28:49,480
But…

395
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:51,780
that can wait.

396
00:28:51,780 --> 00:28:53,520
Good!

397
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:08,180
I am sorry about yesterday.

398
00:29:08,180 --> 00:29:10,780
It wasn't intentional.

399
00:29:12,500 --> 00:29:14,680
It's from my mom.

400
00:29:14,680 --> 00:29:16,460
Eat up.

401
00:29:18,500 --> 00:29:20,200
What?

402
00:29:21,260 --> 00:29:23,900
I am not hungry.

403
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:29,080
How dare you say no after I gave you this?

404
00:29:29,080 --> 00:29:31,420
No manners at all.

405
00:29:33,420 --> 00:29:36,340
I don't think I'm the one who has no manners.

406
00:29:37,100 --> 00:29:39,000
Just eat it.

407
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:40,700
Hey!

408
00:29:41,860 --> 00:29:47,620
Hurry up and eat and teach, so we can go!

409
00:29:47,620 --> 00:29:49,300
Teach?

410
00:29:51,580 --> 00:29:53,460
The class is canceled.

411
00:29:53,460 --> 00:29:57,440
All my students went home already.

412
00:29:57,440 --> 00:29:59,420
There's one left.

413
00:30:04,700 --> 00:30:06,160
No one left.

414
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:07,780
They all went home.

415
00:30:07,780 --> 00:30:09,500
Hey!

416
00:30:09,500 --> 00:30:11,720
My boss said that there is one student left, and that student is you!

417
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:13,300
Idiot!

418
00:30:13,300 --> 00:30:14,900
Do you know that word, Idiot?

419
00:30:14,900 --> 00:30:16,400
Geez, what an idiot!

420
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:19,380
I think that student is Noey.

421
00:30:19,380 --> 00:30:22,620
He meant the student, not the tutor.

422
00:30:25,600 --> 00:30:27,100
Hey!

423
00:30:27,100 --> 00:30:28,940
Is that right, Noey?

424
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:32,320
Who is an idiot now?

425
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:35,380
Oh, are you insulting me?

426
00:30:36,560 --> 00:30:38,740
You're talking about me?

427
00:30:53,440 --> 00:30:54,840
It's the herbal drink.

428
00:30:54,840 --> 00:30:58,420
Do you want me to feed you, or can you eat it by yourself?

429
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:05,980
You don't have to.

430
00:31:05,980 --> 00:31:08,960
I can eat it by myself.

431
00:31:18,600 --> 00:31:20,100
Eat up then.

432
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:24,500
Hurry up.

433
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:30,880
Come on, eat it!

434
00:31:30,880 --> 00:31:32,860
Okay, okay.

435
00:31:40,540 --> 00:31:42,560
It's very good.

436
00:31:48,700 --> 00:31:51,280
Yummy!

437
00:31:52,440 --> 00:31:56,540
Here, drink some water.

438
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:06,700
Yummy!

439
00:32:10,280 --> 00:32:13,160
Which one do your prefer? This one,

440
00:32:13,160 --> 00:32:15,560
or the one you had on the rooftop?

441
00:32:17,260 --> 00:32:19,200
Your cooking?

442
00:32:22,560 --> 00:32:24,100
Rooftop?

443
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:28,040
Well…

444
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:34,680
It's…

445
00:32:35,160 --> 00:32:38,240
It's kinda…

446
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:41,740
- Kinda…
- Hey!

447
00:32:42,560 --> 00:32:45,900
Just spit it out already!

448
00:32:48,880 --> 00:32:50,880
Both are delicious!

449
00:32:50,880 --> 00:32:54,780
Your cooking and your mom's cooking are the same.

450
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:00,640
I thought you would be more honest.

451
00:33:00,640 --> 00:33:02,040
Huh?

452
00:33:06,040 --> 00:33:09,740
My food was not delicious at all.

453
00:33:09,740 --> 00:33:12,480
It's not even as good as my mom's cooking.

454
00:33:14,040 --> 00:33:19,240
Well, it's not that bad.

455
00:33:20,420 --> 00:33:23,100
I will try it again.

456
00:33:23,100 --> 00:33:28,800
I rarely cook, so I still lack experience.

457
00:33:28,800 --> 00:33:30,080
I'll let you try it.

458
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:33,640
And you will forget all about my mom's cooking.

459
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:38,880
Well, so…

460
00:33:38,880 --> 00:33:41,540
Please thank your mom for me.

461
00:33:41,540 --> 00:33:45,000
It's getting dark now. I'd better go.

462
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:46,700
Sit…

463
00:33:47,300 --> 00:33:48,920
Sit down.

464
00:33:50,400 --> 00:33:51,900
Sit down.

465
00:33:59,240 --> 00:34:01,180
Some dessert for you.

466
00:34:01,180 --> 00:34:03,000
You seem to enjoy it.

467
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:05,000
So I bought it for you.

468
00:34:06,040 --> 00:34:06,960
Huh?

469
00:34:06,960 --> 00:34:08,740
Orange.

470
00:34:20,320 --> 00:34:21,640
All right, then.

471
00:34:21,640 --> 00:34:24,020
Go ahead and teach. Whatever you want to teach.

472
00:34:24,020 --> 00:34:26,120
Wait.

473
00:34:26,120 --> 00:34:28,380
You're going to let me teach you?

474
00:34:28,380 --> 00:34:30,380
You silly boy!

475
00:34:30,380 --> 00:34:32,820
Should I be the one teaching you, then?

476
00:34:33,640 --> 00:34:35,760
Real idiot!

477
00:34:39,280 --> 00:34:42,820
I already told you that I won't teach you anymore.

478
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:49,110
It's better if I return the money to you.

479
00:34:49,110 --> 00:34:51,820
So we don't owe each other anything.

480
00:34:51,820 --> 00:34:53,420
Hey!

481
00:34:56,680 --> 00:34:58,780
You won.

482
00:34:58,780 --> 00:35:00,920
I lost.

483
00:35:00,920 --> 00:35:02,460
I must keep the promise.

484
00:35:02,460 --> 00:35:03,940
What promise?

485
00:35:03,940 --> 00:35:08,700
If you win, I'll let you be my tutor with no excuses.

486
00:35:09,560 --> 00:35:11,760
Okay?

487
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:13,700
Do you remember now?

488
00:35:13,700 --> 00:35:15,780
What do you say, Jamnien?

489
00:35:15,780 --> 00:35:18,060
How come I won that?

490
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:23,020
I ran away from the circle.

491
00:35:23,020 --> 00:35:25,440
Before you left,

492
00:35:25,440 --> 00:35:27,920
you punched me in the face.

493
00:35:28,400 --> 00:35:30,120
I lost.

494
00:35:32,420 --> 00:35:34,240
It was just a weak punch. Right?

495
00:35:34,240 --> 00:35:37,280
It doesn't matter weak or strong, you punched my face.

496
00:35:39,200 --> 00:35:41,980
Here, hurry up. I am ready.

497
00:35:41,980 --> 00:35:43,920
I don't know anything.

498
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:46,040
I didn't prepare anything.

499
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:48,740
Well, what do you want me to teach?

500
00:35:48,740 --> 00:35:50,760
What are you studying now?

501
00:35:50,760 --> 00:35:53,300
Or how should we do this…

502
00:35:53,300 --> 00:35:55,720
I am not ready at all.

503
00:35:55,720 --> 00:35:57,780
Can I take a rain check?

504
00:36:00,200 --> 00:36:03,600
If you don't teach me, I won't go back.

505
00:36:05,200 --> 00:36:06,640
Hey.

506
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:08,640
Seriously?

507
00:36:08,640 --> 00:36:10,700
I am not kidding.

508
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:16,640
Well, you can teach me anything.

509
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:18,780
Just any course that you can remember.

510
00:36:18,780 --> 00:36:21,300
Just teach me. Anything!

511
00:36:21,300 --> 00:36:23,500
Anything in the course.

512
00:36:23,500 --> 00:36:25,600
Just pick one.

513
00:36:25,600 --> 00:36:28,120
If you do a great job,

514
00:36:28,120 --> 00:36:29,600
I…

515
00:36:30,120 --> 00:36:32,300
- I will buy you coconut milk ice cream.
- Huh?

516
00:36:33,500 --> 00:36:36,400
I'm trying my best to persuade you.

517
00:36:38,540 --> 00:36:39,700
Hey!

518
00:36:39,700 --> 00:36:41,740
Hurry up and teach him!

519
00:36:41,740 --> 00:36:44,140
Coconut milk ice cream, he said!

520
00:36:44,140 --> 00:36:46,080
He doesn't do that a lot.

521
00:36:46,080 --> 00:36:47,660
You'd be stupid to not take it.

522
00:36:47,660 --> 00:36:49,260
Take it!

523
00:36:56,040 --> 00:36:58,400
You'll go back if I teach you, right?

524
00:37:03,440 --> 00:37:06,320
Well, let's do it this way.

525
00:37:06,320 --> 00:37:10,180
Let's check and see which level we should start from.

526
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:12,540
'Level'?

527
00:37:13,160 --> 00:37:16,540
I think 'level' means difficulty levels of the course.

528
00:37:22,800 --> 00:37:26,840
Do you know what this is?

529
00:37:29,440 --> 00:37:31,180
Circles.

530
00:37:32,060 --> 00:37:33,560
What?

531
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:38,220
Yeah, they're two circles!

532
00:37:38,220 --> 00:37:40,340
Why are you so surprised?

533
00:37:54,120 --> 00:37:58,780
Um… What do you see in this picture?

534
00:37:58,780 --> 00:38:01,020
- Circles.
- Two circles.

535
00:38:01,020 --> 00:38:04,780
Yeah, if they're not circles, then what the heck are they?

536
00:38:04,780 --> 00:38:08,540
Hey, what's with you and those circles?

537
00:38:08,540 --> 00:38:10,940
You didn't finish our lessons yesterday either.

538
00:38:10,940 --> 00:38:14,180
Why did you take that long?

539
00:38:14,180 --> 00:38:18,300
Do you think I should waste my time

540
00:38:18,300 --> 00:38:22,600
just to learn about these circles?

541
00:38:22,600 --> 00:38:23,580
Gosh…

542
00:38:23,580 --> 00:38:25,680
Wish I could say it out loud.

543
00:38:25,680 --> 00:38:28,220
But I am afraid they'll beat me up.

544
00:39:11,740 --> 00:39:16,740
From now on, we will study about… union and intersection!

545
00:39:26,380 --> 00:39:28,120
Whatever!

546
00:39:28,120 --> 00:39:31,220
There's no turning back now. I am a teacher.

547
00:39:31,220 --> 00:39:33,580
I can't choose who I'd like to teach.

